The firm must have empanelled with major PSUs audit as per C & AG for FY 2020-21 or latest  & RBI for FY 2019-20 or latest .
The firm shall be in existence for at least 10 years practicing chartered accountant, register with ICAI.

c.	The firm shall be Partnership firms with One full time FCA. The partnership concern shall be in continuous practice for the period of minimum 10 years. Joint Venture & A.O.P. (Association of Persons) firms are not allowed.
The firm should have annual minimum turnover* of Rs. 35.00 lakhs each year in preceding 03 years i.e. F.Y 2017-18, 2018-19 and 2019-20.
The firm must have experience of working in all at least 02 Govt./PSU assignment for Statutory Audit in preceding 04 years between F.Y. 2017-18 to 2020-21.
The firm must have goods and service tax registration.
The firm must have filed income tax Returns for preceding 03 years for the F.Y. i.e. 2017-18,  2018-19 and 2019-20.
The firm must have audit team, of minimum 06 (Articles /audit clerk) and other audit staff who have qualified the Intermediate/ PE II/PCC/IPCC Examination of the ICAI.
It is necessary to have at least minimum 04 full time chartered accountant Partners/Employees as on date of advertisement in the firm.
The head office of the firm must be in the State of Bihar
The C.A. Firm who has conducted the Statutory Audit of Bihar Education Project Council. Patna continues for three year, will not be entitled for Statutory Audit in F.Y. 2021-22.
The C.A. Firm who has conducted the concurrent audit of Bihar Education Project Council, Patna for the year 2021-22, will not be entitled for Statutory Audit in the F.Y. 2021-22.
